      "name": "finished(stream[, callback])",
      "kind": "function",
      "status": "partial",
      "notes": "Supports callback-oriented completion/error observation for the current Readable, Writable, Duplex, Transform, and PassThrough implementations by monitoring end, finish, error, and premature close signals. An optional options object with `signal` cancels the observer with `AbortError`. Omitting the callback returns the same Promise-backed observer used by `node:stream/promises`.",
